<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id121e2940-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s512"><num value="512">§ 512.</num><heading> Approval of paper contracts; time for performance; bonds</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A contract for furnishing paper is not valid until approved by the Joint Committee on Printing. The award of a contract for furnishing paper shall designate a reasonable time for its performance. The contractor shall give bond in an amount fixed and approved by the Committee.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id121e2941-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1244">82 Stat. 1244</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
